abstract: >
  A Python library implementing a discrete convolution engine for generating 
  Log-Tower polynomials P(An) and P(Rn). This tool replaces recursive 
  differentiation with a cached F-Kernel (Omega) approach, enabling O(n^3) 
  complexity for high-order derivatives of hÂ·ln(g)/ln(f). It includes a 
  verification suite and supports symbolic output via SymPy.
